1
00:00:09,333 --> 00:00:11,416
[YUMA]
Anyone seen Hinomaru?

2
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:12,958
[OZEKI]
Yeah.

3
00:00:13,041 --> 00:00:15,041
The doc called him and the Coach
into the back office.

4
00:00:16,375 --> 00:00:17,916
-It's pretty amazing.
-Hmm?

5
00:00:19,083 --> 00:00:21,583
Us. Actually winning.
We did it.

6
00:00:21,666 --> 00:00:23,583
We brought down Hakuro.

7
00:00:24,625 --> 00:00:26,291
Dachi beat Hakuro!

8
00:00:26,375 --> 00:00:28,458
The strongest club
in high school sumo!

9
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,083
[cheering]

10
00:00:30,166 --> 00:00:32,416
You started off your fight
like a bad-ass!

11
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:34,375
Man, it got me so pumped up!

12
00:00:34,458 --> 00:00:37,125
Just walking away
from that gorilla like that.

13
00:00:37,208 --> 00:00:38,458
Stop it.

14
00:00:38,541 --> 00:00:40,041
I lost my bout.

15
00:00:40,125 --> 00:00:41,750
What about you, Kunisaki?

16
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:43,708
That makes two national
treasures you've conquered!

17
00:00:43,791 --> 00:00:45,125
[CHIHIRO]
I know, right?

18
00:00:45,208 --> 00:00:47,666
I've been on one hell
of a winning streak!

19
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:49,333
Not saying I'm even interested,

20
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:51,583
but what if they choose me
to go to the All-Japan?

21
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:54,041
I'm so good, I scare myself!

22
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:57,166
Not again!

23
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:58,750
Stupid nosebleeds.

24
00:01:00,375 --> 00:01:01,625
-Here.
-Good timing!

25
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,458
Tsuruko with the save!

26
00:01:03,541 --> 00:01:04,916
My name's Chizuko.

27
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,166
How are all you guys
joking around?

28
00:01:07,250 --> 00:01:10,291
I put every ounce of energy
I had into that last bout.

29
00:01:11,541 --> 00:01:13,166
You did great, by the way.

30
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:15,500
Even with all that pressure,
you took care of things.

31
00:01:15,583 --> 00:01:17,333
Don't act like you weren't
partly to blame.

32
00:01:17,416 --> 00:01:18,458
Huh?

33
00:01:18,541 --> 00:01:19,958
[YUMA]
When you lost your match,

34
00:01:20,041 --> 00:01:21,958
I thought my heart was gonna
burst out of my chest.

35
00:01:22,041 --> 00:01:23,166
[OZEKI laughs]

36
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:24,541
It motivated you though.

37
00:01:27,208 --> 00:01:28,750
[REINA]
I know I should be overjoyed

38
00:01:28,833 --> 00:01:30,375
at what we've accomplished

39
00:01:30,458 --> 00:01:32,875
and busy celebrating our victory
with the rest of the team.

40
00:01:33,875 --> 00:01:36,583
But why do I feel so uneasy?

41
00:01:37,583 --> 00:01:39,416
Yeah. We really did it.

42
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,416
Made it all the way
to the final

43
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,708
and achieved our biggest goal.

44
00:01:43,791 --> 00:01:46,750
Giving Hinomaru a chance
to face Kuze in the ring.

45
00:01:47,791 --> 00:01:50,791
It doesn't matter if we lose
as a team at this point.

46
00:01:50,875 --> 00:01:52,500
As long as he can take
the fifth bout,

47
00:01:52,583 --> 00:01:55,125
his dream of going pro
is still a possibility.

48
00:01:57,291 --> 00:01:59,166
Hell, so what if we lose?

49
00:01:59,250 --> 00:02:00,958
We're still silver.

50
00:02:01,041 --> 00:02:03,291
Second place at our first
national tournament!

51
00:02:03,375 --> 00:02:05,041
Sorry, second place?

52
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,291
We've already beat
the strongest team!

53
00:02:07,375 --> 00:02:10,875
Eiga's gonna be a cake walk
compared to Hakuro!

54
00:02:10,958 --> 00:02:12,541
What're you...

55
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:13,791
[REINA]
That's it.

56
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:15,666
I know what's wrong.

57
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:21,000
-They're slacking.
-[YUMA grunts]

58
00:02:21,083 --> 00:02:22,375
Gah!

59
00:02:23,666 --> 00:02:26,166
You're all acting like the
tournament's already finished!

60
00:02:26,250 --> 00:02:27,708
Are you forgetting?

61
00:02:27,791 --> 00:02:30,250
Hinomaru's got a lot
of battles left to fight!

62
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,458
So what's this talk about
how losing doesn't matter

63
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:34,375
or how easy
it will be to win?

64
00:02:34,458 --> 00:02:36,458
You can't just sit back
and relax now!

65
00:02:37,458 --> 00:02:39,750
Know why Hinomaru
defeated Tennoji?

66
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:42,166
Because he saw how hard
you guys fought for him!

67
00:02:43,166 --> 00:02:45,208
That's where he gets
his strength!

68
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:49,250
And Kuze, he's an even
stronger opponent.

69
00:02:50,541 --> 00:02:53,541
I'm not sure if even
Hinomaru can beat him.

70
00:02:53,625 --> 00:02:55,833
So fight!
And don't settle!

71
00:02:55,916 --> 00:02:57,041
Try your hardest to win,

72
00:02:57,125 --> 00:02:58,875
if not for yourselves,
then for him!

73
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,375
[ALL groan]

74
00:03:01,791 --> 00:03:03,916
Uh... Yeah.

75
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,208
I mean...

76
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:06,708
Why'd you open your mouth?

77
00:03:07,750 --> 00:03:09,041
But obviously,
I'm not in the ring

78
00:03:09,125 --> 00:03:11,416
and it's not my place
to criticize anyone.

79
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:14,791
So, um, good work
and I'm sorry for ranting.

80
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,250
-[OZEKI] No.
-Huh?

81
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:19,291
You were absolutely right
to speak up.

82
00:03:19,375 --> 00:03:22,208
Thanks for telling them what
I should've said as captain.

83
00:03:23,625 --> 00:03:25,666
It probably slipped our minds.

84
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:27,958
Ushio lost in
the individual tournament,

85
00:03:28,041 --> 00:03:31,000
so even if he beats Kuze,
he may not get invited

86
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:33,500
to the All-Japan
National Championships.

87
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:35,875
We need to do all we can
to increase his chances,

88
00:03:35,958 --> 00:03:38,208
even if it's only
by a small amount.

89
00:03:38,291 --> 00:03:40,625
We'll make Dachi High
the top team in Japan!

90
00:03:40,708 --> 00:03:43,541
And help Ushio become
the number one wrestler

91
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:46,083
from the best school
in the country!

92
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:48,125
It won't be just
for his sake, either.

93
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:50,541
I know, our team has
the potential

94
00:03:50,625 --> 00:03:52,375
to be the best there is!

95
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:56,208
Win or lose,
this is our final match!

96
00:03:57,208 --> 00:03:58,250
Guys.

97
00:03:58,333 --> 00:04:00,208
Let's go and make
that dream real!

98
00:04:00,291 --> 00:04:02,125
[ALL]
Yeah!

99
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,291
[HINOMARU]
Yeah!

100
00:04:03,375 --> 00:04:05,416
Um, how much of that
did you hear?

101
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:06,583
Ha, ha, ha.

102
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,916
[HINOMARU] It's the last time
this team will fight together.

103
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,625
Know what I think?

104
00:04:12,708 --> 00:04:13,875
We've got what it takes.

105
00:04:13,958 --> 00:04:15,250
♪

106
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,166
We'll be the best in Japan!

107
00:05:51,916 --> 00:05:53,125
Hands on the ground!

108
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:55,875
Spirit!

109
00:05:55,958 --> 00:05:57,666
[BOTH grunting]

110
00:06:00,208 --> 00:06:02,000
Pure railroad tracks.

111
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:04,541
That was quick.
These are the semis, right?

112
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:06,083
[sighs]

113
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,041
Pff!

114
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:08,208
[grunts]

115
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,916
The second bout
didn't last long either.

116
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:15,833
Same for the third.

117
00:06:17,333 --> 00:06:18,916
And the fourth.

118
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,625
Four straight
railroad track wins.

119
00:06:20,708 --> 00:06:22,250
No surprise.

120
00:06:22,333 --> 00:06:23,583
They're huge.

121
00:06:23,666 --> 00:06:27,083
♪

122
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,291
[gasps]

123
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:31,666
♪

124
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:37,458
Aah!

125
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:40,291
-[REFEREE] Spirit!
-[KUZE growls]

126
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:42,333
[screams]

127
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:44,958
The bout is concluded!

128
00:06:45,041 --> 00:06:46,500
[CROWD cheers]

129
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:49,541
He was so intimidated,
he retreated out of the ring.

130
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:51,041
The ol' stare-out.

131
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:53,541
Centuries ago, that used to be

132
00:06:53,625 --> 00:06:55,041
the way you determined
the winner.

133
00:06:56,041 --> 00:06:58,666
They were outmatched.
You can only pity them.

134
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:02,625
He's not even in the same realm
as high school sumo anymore.

135
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:07,041
♪

136
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:10,166
Well, if it isn't
this year's dark horse.

137
00:07:12,541 --> 00:07:14,541
[OZEKI] Back when we trained
with them before,

138
00:07:14,625 --> 00:07:16,625
we didn't stand a chance.

139
00:07:17,791 --> 00:07:20,750
I had no idea we'd be fighting
their team in the final!

140
00:07:22,041 --> 00:07:26,541
Meeting again face-to-face,
I'm reminded how huge they are.

141
00:07:26,625 --> 00:07:29,250
It's been far too long, Chihiro.

142
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:32,208
Sorry I missed you
that one time we practiced.

143
00:07:32,291 --> 00:07:35,625
But maybe your heart's more
into academics than sumo, huh?

144
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:39,083
Come on, I'm just messin'
with ya!

145
00:07:39,166 --> 00:07:41,125
You and me,
we're all good, right?

146
00:07:41,208 --> 00:07:42,708
I mean, you took up sumo.

147
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:45,083
Why else would you,
unless you looked up to me?

148
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:48,000
Me getting into sumo had zero
to do with you, got it?

149
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:50,333
My hate for you burns
like the sun.

150
00:07:50,416 --> 00:07:53,541
And I'll keep hating you
until you die.

151
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:55,750
[OZEKI] Well, they seem
to know each other.

152
00:07:55,833 --> 00:07:57,791
Maybe they're like friends?

153
00:07:57,875 --> 00:08:00,083
-[DANIEL] Calm down, everyone.
-Huh?

154
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:02,625
There's no need for us
to be aggressive.

155
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:05,958
The way I see it, sumo is more
of a beautiful endeavor

156
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:07,625
and less of a fight.

157
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,333
Leon, you agree, right?

158
00:08:09,416 --> 00:08:11,375
Dude, are you insane?

159
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:13,250
Sumo is nothing but fighting!

160
00:08:13,333 --> 00:08:15,875
I swear, if you say beautiful
one more time!

161
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:18,375
Whatever our
personal philosophies are,

162
00:08:18,458 --> 00:08:20,083
let's save it
for the bouts, cool?

163
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,708
[HYODO]
Just one last thing, Odachi.

164
00:08:22,791 --> 00:08:24,750
Looks like you're one man short.

165
00:08:24,833 --> 00:08:28,000
Can we expect to see that runt
Mitsuhashi in the final?

166
00:08:28,083 --> 00:08:29,958
[SAWAI]
Fat chance of that happening.

167
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:32,250
The twig didn't know his limits
and got snapped.

168
00:08:32,333 --> 00:08:33,375
He had it coming.

169
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:35,625
He needs to accept
the hard truth.

170
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:37,333
Sumo wrestlers have to be big,

171
00:08:37,416 --> 00:08:39,208
heavy, and larger
than life itself.

172
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,208
You'll understand what I mean
soon enough

173
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:43,125
after we meet each other
inside the ring.

174
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:45,291
Hold on a minute.

175
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:46,625
Hmm?

176
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:48,875
Do you actually believe
what you just said?

177
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,375
After all, you've seen
what our number five can do.

178
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:53,000
♪

179
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,333
There's something you don't get.

180
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:58,125
Sumo doesn't boil down to size
and weight alone.

181
00:08:58,208 --> 00:08:59,708
It's about spirit.

182
00:08:59,791 --> 00:09:01,625
♪

183
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:04,583
You ought to save that line
for later.

184
00:09:04,666 --> 00:09:07,083
Like maybe after you've beaten
our number five.

185
00:09:07,166 --> 00:09:09,958
♪

186
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,458
We don't hold back.

187
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:17,958
It's to the death, then.

188
00:09:19,458 --> 00:09:23,000
His victory in the individual
tournament was hard-fought.

189
00:09:23,083 --> 00:09:24,125
True.

190
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:27,250
♪

191
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:34,333
Quite the high school yokozuna
this year.

192
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:36,083
A national treasure
who also happens

193
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:38,833
to be the son
of the famous Yamatokuni.

194
00:09:38,916 --> 00:09:40,875
There's so much going for him,
he may be ready

195
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,750
to move straight
into the pro league.

196
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,625
In other words,
this bout coming up

197
00:09:44,708 --> 00:09:46,791
will be Hinomaru's
final opportunity

198
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:49,250
to compete with him
at the high school level.

199
00:09:50,375 --> 00:09:52,208
The individual tournament
is done.

200
00:09:53,416 --> 00:09:55,958
However, the strongest
sumo wrestler

201
00:09:56,041 --> 00:09:57,250
has yet to be determined.

202
00:09:58,500 --> 00:10:01,083
We'll find that out
in the team tournament final.

203
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,375
In the fifth and last bout.

204
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,666
Isn't that right, Hinomaru?

205
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,166
[grunting]

206
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:12,125
It's about time.
Let's get going.

207
00:10:12,208 --> 00:10:13,250
[HINOMARU]
Ready!

208
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:15,333
Best of luck out there,
you guys.

209
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:17,250
-Yeah!
-We've got this!

210
00:10:24,916 --> 00:10:28,083
And remember to have fun...
Hinomaru.

211
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,916
Oops. Was that not
the right thing to say?

212
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,916
Sorry if I broke
your concentration.

213
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,541
Um. I meant,
"good luck, Shorty!"

214
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:38,333
[CROWD cheering in distance]

215
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:42,291
[HINOMARU]
"Have fun." Huh.

216
00:10:43,625 --> 00:10:44,833
Will do!

217
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:47,041
♪

218
00:10:47,125 --> 00:10:48,750
[ANNOUNCER]
The team tournament final.

219
00:10:48,833 --> 00:10:51,333
On the east side,
Odachi High School.

220
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:54,333
[CROWD cheers]

221
00:10:54,416 --> 00:10:57,916
♪

222
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,166
[ANNOUNCER]
On the west side,

223
00:10:59,250 --> 00:11:00,916
Eiga University High School.

224
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,041
[CROWD cheers]

225
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:06,000
It really happened.

226
00:11:06,083 --> 00:11:07,666
Dachi's in the final round.

227
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:09,500
Yeah, maybe, but strategically,

228
00:11:09,583 --> 00:11:11,458
Eiga's definitely got
the advantage.

229
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:12,708
You aren't wrong.

230
00:11:12,791 --> 00:11:14,833
You've got two teams.

231
00:11:14,916 --> 00:11:17,458
One that sailed through the
semi-finals without a scratch

232
00:11:17,541 --> 00:11:19,916
and one that got totally
pummeled in the last round.

233
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:24,000
Plus, they've revealed
all their secret weapons.

234
00:11:24,083 --> 00:11:26,291
This match will come down
to one factor.

235
00:11:26,375 --> 00:11:27,875
The most spirit.

236
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:30,250
That's why they're gonna try
to hit the ground running.

237
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,500
♪

238
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:35,541
Go out and get us our first win!

239
00:11:35,625 --> 00:11:37,291
[ANNOUNCER]
On the east side, Kunisaki.

240
00:11:37,375 --> 00:11:39,291
[CROWD cheers]

241
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:41,083
All those adoring fans.

242
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:42,416
Such a crowd pleaser.

243
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,041
Isn't that right, Chihiro?

244
00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:45,833
[ANNOUNCER]
On the west side, Hyodo.

245
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:47,041
[CROWD cheers]

246
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:48,333
Well.

247
00:11:48,416 --> 00:11:50,500
I suppose beating
two national treasures

248
00:11:50,583 --> 00:11:52,375
should count for something.

249
00:11:52,458 --> 00:11:54,875
And so soon after joining sumo.

250
00:11:54,958 --> 00:11:56,500
I'm impressed.

251
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:58,500
-Doesn't matter though.
-Huh?

252
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:00,000
[HYODO]
Let's be real, here.

253
00:12:00,083 --> 00:12:02,791
You think you're gonna outshine
your older brother?

254
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:04,500
Dream on.

255
00:12:06,041 --> 00:12:08,833
You're seriously telling us
Hyodo's your older brother?

256
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:11,791
The folks went through the whole
divorce thing when I was five.

257
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:14,833
Hyodo went off
to live with our father.

258
00:12:14,916 --> 00:12:17,583
I hated the guy, so I decided
to stay with my mother.

259
00:12:17,666 --> 00:12:20,208
Now he's back in my life again.

260
00:12:20,291 --> 00:12:21,500
That jerk.

261
00:12:22,750 --> 00:12:24,000
[mocking laughter]

262
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:29,583
My only memories of him
are of a pre-teen bully.

263
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:30,833
No one else.

264
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,916
It's going to be me
who takes him on!

265
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,916
I've waited too long for this!

266
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,708
♪

267
00:12:36,791 --> 00:12:38,375
Place your hands on the ground!

268
00:12:39,416 --> 00:12:41,250
The two brothers are similar.

269
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:44,625
Both have latent sumo talents
on par with a national treasure.

270
00:12:46,125 --> 00:12:49,000
But like I said,
only on par with.

271
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:50,541
There's something specific
keeping him

272
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:51,958
from joining their ranks.

273
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:54,458
Hey, bro, gotta say.

274
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:57,791
I'm a real huge fan
of that Mitsuhashi kid.

275
00:12:57,875 --> 00:13:00,375
That move he pulled
in the semi-finals,

276
00:13:00,458 --> 00:13:02,541
it took brass balls!

277
00:13:02,625 --> 00:13:05,000
There's a reason
he hasn't earned a moniker?

278
00:13:05,083 --> 00:13:06,416
Yeah.

279
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,708
A big one.

280
00:13:09,083 --> 00:13:10,291
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

281
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,208
[ALL gasp]

282
00:13:14,291 --> 00:13:15,583
What?

283
00:13:20,833 --> 00:13:22,083
[KIRIHITO]
He's an idiot.

284
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:28,083
So, what d'ya think, Chihiro?

285
00:13:28,166 --> 00:13:29,791
Bet you're impressed.

286
00:13:29,875 --> 00:13:32,541
Go ahead.
Lose your cool and charge at me.

287
00:13:32,625 --> 00:13:34,833
I'll leap outta the way.
[screams]

288
00:13:34,916 --> 00:13:36,708
He just stood there,
what the hell?

289
00:13:36,791 --> 00:13:38,750
Hyodo, you are king
of the idiots!

290
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:40,875
Whoa! Whoa! Hold on!

291
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:42,541
He's tricky.

292
00:13:42,625 --> 00:13:45,541
To the point, he ends up digging
his own grave occasionally.

293
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,000
-But...
-You dick!

294
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:49,666
I said wait!

295
00:13:49,750 --> 00:13:52,083
That's how he's able
to take down opponents!

296
00:13:52,166 --> 00:13:54,416
Strength and unpredictability!

297
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:57,666
It'd do you good to listen to
your older brother for a change.

298
00:13:57,750 --> 00:13:58,958
You paying attention?

299
00:14:00,000 --> 00:14:02,875
[KIRIHITO] The only one who can
fight an idiot of his caliber...

300
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:05,250
[CHIHIRO]
Leap!

301
00:14:06,458 --> 00:14:08,250
[KIRIHITO]
...is another idiot!

302
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:09,416
[ALL gasp]

303
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,083
What the hell kinda bout
is this?

304
00:14:12,166 --> 00:14:14,208
[CHIHIRO] He's always stealing
the things I love

305
00:14:14,291 --> 00:14:15,916
and ruining them for me!

306
00:14:16,916 --> 00:14:17,958
Huh?

307
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:19,750
You're taking up boxing now?

308
00:14:19,833 --> 00:14:21,583
Hey, the two of us
should have a match.

309
00:14:21,666 --> 00:14:23,250
-[HYODO grunts]
-[CHIHIRO groans]

310
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:25,583
-[bell dings]
-Oh, is it over already?

311
00:14:27,958 --> 00:14:31,875
[CHIHIRO] He bulldozes my world,
then waltzes off!

312
00:14:31,958 --> 00:14:33,458
Not this time!

313
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:36,208
Dachi High's dream
is to be the best in Japan!

314
00:14:36,291 --> 00:14:38,166
You won't take that away!

315
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:41,458
Good idea.
Think I'll jump too!

316
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:42,625
What the...

317
00:14:42,708 --> 00:14:44,375
He's mocking me!

318
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,083
♪

319
00:14:46,166 --> 00:14:49,166
If you're not gonna let me
grab your belt, then...

320
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,791
Flash Attack!

321
00:14:50,875 --> 00:14:53,500
You like that, bro?

322
00:14:53,583 --> 00:14:56,125
-Masato Hyodo?
-Huh?

323
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:57,708
Is there a problem, Kunisaki?

324
00:14:58,750 --> 00:15:01,333
Um, no.
So what about him?

325
00:15:01,416 --> 00:15:04,625
He's been wrestling two years,
but in that short amount of time

326
00:15:04,708 --> 00:15:06,458
he's already earned
a spot as a regular

327
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:07,708
on the Eiga High team.

328
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,625
This is from
the spring tournament.

329
00:15:10,708 --> 00:15:13,916
As you can see, his technique
is highly unpredictable.

330
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:16,750
He's got power, speed,
and killer instincts.

331
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:19,166
All his stats are first-class.

332
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:21,250
It's your second year, huh?

333
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:22,875
Well, this is only my first!

334
00:15:22,958 --> 00:15:24,750
-[CHIHIRO groaning]
-[HYODO laughing]

335
00:15:24,833 --> 00:15:27,541
[CHIHIRO] You'd always take up
whatever sport I was into.

336
00:15:27,625 --> 00:15:29,291
Outdo me, then quit!

337
00:15:30,708 --> 00:15:32,708
But this time, it's my turn!

338
00:15:32,791 --> 00:15:34,458
I've only done this one year

339
00:15:34,541 --> 00:15:37,375
and already beaten
two national treasures!

340
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:38,791
[HYODO]
Hey, you're not half bad!

341
00:15:38,875 --> 00:15:40,875
Whoa! Can't see.

342
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:42,958
[HYODO]
Down you go!

343
00:15:43,041 --> 00:15:44,125
Inner foot sweep!

344
00:15:44,208 --> 00:15:46,000
Remember, those are
my techniques

345
00:15:46,083 --> 00:15:47,291
you're representing out there.

346
00:15:47,375 --> 00:15:49,458
You'd better do them justice,
Kunisaki!

347
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:53,041
[CHIHIRO]
Damn. Spider monkey!

348
00:15:53,125 --> 00:15:55,708
A leg grab, huh?
No good!

349
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,000
Got ya!

350
00:15:58,083 --> 00:15:59,750
Yaaah!

351
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:01,708
Grab some dirt!

352
00:16:01,791 --> 00:16:03,708
You're insane!
This is serious!

353
00:16:03,791 --> 00:16:05,041
Quit screwing around!

354
00:16:05,125 --> 00:16:07,625
It looks to me like
you're losing your cool!

355
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:09,458
Chihiro!

356
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:11,916
[CHIHIRO]
An overarm throw?

357
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:14,541
Did you see that, Ref?

358
00:16:15,833 --> 00:16:16,958
Running away?

359
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:18,708
[BOTH grunting]

360
00:16:18,791 --> 00:16:20,083
A test of strength!

361
00:16:20,166 --> 00:16:22,750
Can you call what they're doing
sumo anymore?

362
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:24,333
Incredible!

363
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:25,291
[KIRIHITO]
What's going on?

364
00:16:25,375 --> 00:16:26,958
You need to relax!

365
00:16:27,041 --> 00:16:30,166
If you just regain focus,
you can win this bout easily!

366
00:16:30,250 --> 00:16:32,791
Why'd you go and pinch me,
you cheating cheater?

367
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,458
It just popped into my head
so I had to try it!

368
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:37,541
Damn it.

369
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:39,708
Be serious for once in your...

370
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:40,833
Holy crap.

371
00:16:42,291 --> 00:16:44,041
[HINOMARU]
This Hyodo guy's something else.

372
00:16:45,291 --> 00:16:47,250
You can tell
how much he loves sumo.

373
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:50,166
[CHIHIRO] With all
his stupid running around,

374
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:51,458
it was hard to notice,

375
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:53,458
but up close, it's clear.

376
00:16:53,541 --> 00:16:55,375
The brother who always used
to get bored

377
00:16:55,458 --> 00:16:57,333
and walk away
has been working out,

378
00:16:57,416 --> 00:17:01,041
transforming his body
into a sumo wrestler!

379
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:02,666
[sighs]

380
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:06,000
[YOMODA] Watching Hyodo fight
is giving me a coronary.

381
00:17:06,083 --> 00:17:07,750
He'll defeat someone
twice as strong,

382
00:17:07,833 --> 00:17:10,208
and then turn around
and lose to an easy opponent.

383
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:13,291
Makes it difficult to predict
how many bouts

384
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:15,833
you're going to win
during a team match.

385
00:17:15,916 --> 00:17:19,291
Still, the guy only took up sumo
two years ago.

386
00:17:20,916 --> 00:17:23,041
Back in those days,
he'd join a club,

387
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:24,875
make a scene, get kicked out.

388
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:26,750
Rinse and repeat.

389
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,791
Until he found ours.

390
00:17:28,875 --> 00:17:32,083
He challenged us to a fight and
was knocked flat on his back.

391
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:35,833
So this is sumo wrestling, huh?

392
00:17:35,916 --> 00:17:37,416
It's my kind of sport.

393
00:17:38,750 --> 00:17:41,291
He's an idiot,
don't get me wrong.

394
00:17:41,375 --> 00:17:42,750
Thing is...

395
00:17:42,833 --> 00:17:44,375
the guy's in love with it.

396
00:17:44,458 --> 00:17:47,500
His passion is so intense,
it makes you want to back off...

397
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,833
and just let him do his thing.

398
00:17:50,916 --> 00:17:52,750
[straining]

399
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:54,083
[HYODO]
Chihiro,

400
00:17:54,166 --> 00:17:55,833
do you love sumo?

401
00:17:55,916 --> 00:17:58,041
Don't laugh, but I know I do.

402
00:17:58,125 --> 00:17:59,833
I finally found
what was missing.

403
00:17:59,916 --> 00:18:02,291
That thing in life
that makes me proud of who I am.

404
00:18:03,375 --> 00:18:05,208
What about you?

405
00:18:05,291 --> 00:18:07,666
What's your reason
for joining the club?

406
00:18:09,833 --> 00:18:12,833
[CHIHIRO] It was the day
I lost to Hinomaru.

407
00:18:12,916 --> 00:18:15,625
I wanted to learn
how he managed to beat me.

408
00:18:15,708 --> 00:18:18,916
But I've kept telling myself
it's like wrestling.

409
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,291
Just another step
on my journey to being

410
00:18:21,375 --> 00:18:23,916
the top mixed martial arts
fighter in the world.

411
00:18:26,125 --> 00:18:29,416
Who do I think I am
compared to Hinomaru?

412
00:18:29,500 --> 00:18:31,708
Or any of the other
national treasures?

413
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:34,416
Chihiro...

414
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,500
I see you out there
overthinking things.

415
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:38,875
Trust your feelings.

416
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,250
Yeah!

417
00:18:43,333 --> 00:18:44,458
[CHIHIRO]
Know what?

418
00:18:44,541 --> 00:18:46,208
My answer's the same!

419
00:18:46,291 --> 00:18:47,958
[KIRIHITO]
He's changing tactics!

420
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:50,000
He lowered his head
and is charging in!

421
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:51,791
[BOTH grunt]

422
00:18:51,875 --> 00:18:54,833
[CHIHIRO]
I love sumo!

423
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,208
[KIRIHITO]
He doesn't have sharp footwork

424
00:18:56,291 --> 00:18:58,666
or shift techniques
like Hinomaru.

425
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:00,291
It's just a matter
of time before...

426
00:19:02,875 --> 00:19:04,000
[CHIHIRO]
That's right.

427
00:19:04,083 --> 00:19:06,125
I've never worked
on my headbutting.

428
00:19:06,208 --> 00:19:08,333
I sidelined it to focus
on winning!

429
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:12,583
But I had to try,
even if the odds were slim!

430
00:19:12,666 --> 00:19:15,833
It was that or run away
from sumo!

431
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:18,416
[BOTH straining]

432
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,500
Guys, I'm sorry.

433
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,916
I could've sworn you wanted
to be the strongest!

434
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,708
Fight back, Kunisaki!

435
00:19:26,791 --> 00:19:28,166
You're the best improviser!

436
00:19:28,250 --> 00:19:29,875
And the strongest in sumo!

437
00:19:29,958 --> 00:19:31,625
So don't lose this!

438
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,291
[CHIHIRO]
Supreme! Invincible!

439
00:19:34,375 --> 00:19:37,000
And the strongest!

440
00:19:37,083 --> 00:19:39,500
Clasped hand twist drop throw!

441
00:19:39,583 --> 00:19:42,500
Neo Chihiro Special Number Two!

442
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:45,833
I was wondering when you
were gonna try that!

443
00:19:45,916 --> 00:19:47,875
Sorry to break it to you,

444
00:19:47,958 --> 00:19:49,583
but you're not the only one

445
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:52,375
who knows both wrestling
and sumo techniques!

446
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:53,708
[ALL gasp]

447
00:19:53,791 --> 00:19:55,125
[REFEREE]
West side wins!

448
00:19:55,208 --> 00:19:56,625
[CROWD cheering]

449
00:19:56,708 --> 00:19:57,666
Tss!

450
00:19:58,666 --> 00:20:01,958
Going with the headbutt put him
at a pretty severe disadvantage.

451
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:03,291
Yeah.

452
00:20:03,375 --> 00:20:05,416
When you break the teams
down by physiques.

453
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:08,916
Between Dachi and Eiga,
there's no competition.

454
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,625
I get that, but still.

455
00:20:10,708 --> 00:20:13,750
There wasn't a huge difference
in size during the first bout.

456
00:20:13,833 --> 00:20:16,375
Actually, what impressed me
the most

457
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:18,708
was how Hyodo handled
that last throw.

458
00:20:18,791 --> 00:20:21,458
-Those two are so similar.
-[HYODO panting]

459
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:24,541
Maybe they each understood
what the other was about.

460
00:20:24,625 --> 00:20:28,500
Well, looks like
I bested you again,

461
00:20:28,583 --> 00:20:29,666
little brother.

462
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:34,333
I don't think I hate anyone
more than you.

463
00:20:34,416 --> 00:20:36,166
You always ate my food,

464
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:39,500
used my save data
to beat my video games.

465
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:42,208
Oh, and let's not forget
about taking my allowance.

466
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:44,166
But what pisses me off
the most...

467
00:20:45,166 --> 00:20:47,958
Is having to admit that you're
actually pretty strong.

468
00:20:48,041 --> 00:20:49,041
Huh?

469
00:20:51,041 --> 00:20:53,333
I'm not sure what
you're talking about,

470
00:20:53,416 --> 00:20:54,958
but that match we had

471
00:20:55,041 --> 00:20:56,583
was kick-ass! Right?

472
00:20:57,583 --> 00:20:59,333
Yeah, I guess so.

473
00:21:01,875 --> 00:21:03,416
Oh, man.

474
00:21:03,500 --> 00:21:05,083
That was a big loss.

475
00:21:05,166 --> 00:21:07,583
Their team must be in shock
after that.

476
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:09,958
-No doubt.
-You really think so?

477
00:21:11,333 --> 00:21:14,166
You could've won that bout
if you didn't get so worked up.

478
00:21:14,250 --> 00:21:15,916
Yeah, my bad.

479
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:19,125
I'm counting on you
to make it up.

480
00:21:20,416 --> 00:21:22,166
During our practice sessions,

481
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:24,000
there were only two
Dachi High members

482
00:21:24,083 --> 00:21:25,833
I could never beat.

483
00:21:25,916 --> 00:21:27,833
One was Hinomaru.

484
00:21:27,916 --> 00:21:29,416
And the second was...

485
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:31,875
[KIRIHITO] I wasn't expecting
to start with a loss.

486
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,333
Looks like I've no choice
but to adapt.

487
00:21:36,458 --> 00:21:37,583
[ANNOUNCER]
Second bout.

488
00:21:37,666 --> 00:21:40,000
On the east side, Tsuji.

489
00:23:12,958 --> 00:23:14,208
-Morning!
-[KUZE] Hmm?

490
00:23:14,291 --> 00:23:16,208
You and me!
Arm wrestling! Now!

491
00:23:16,291 --> 00:23:17,916
Yeah, I don't arm wrestle.

492
00:23:18,958 --> 00:23:20,208
-What's up!
-[KUZE] Hmm?

493
00:23:20,291 --> 00:23:21,833
Me, you, thumb wrestlin'!

494
00:23:21,916 --> 00:23:23,875
I don't really
thumb wrestle either.

495
00:23:23,958 --> 00:23:27,166
So what kinda wrestling
do you do?

496
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:28,166
Hmm?

497
00:23:28,250 --> 00:23:29,958
♪

498
00:23:31,958 --> 00:23:33,416
[grunts]

499
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:35,875
Why didn't you tell me you were
an expert at this game?

500
00:23:35,958 --> 00:23:37,250
What is this?

